1. Go to Sass-lang.com

To install Sass You need Node js installed on your device
Go to https://nodejs.org/en/download/ and install it on your device

I have already installed on my device

2. Open command prompt and
Type this command

npm install -g sass [This will install sass gloabally on your device]

3. Open VS code
Search in Marketplace Live SASS compiler

4. Install it

5. While working on Project create filename.scss and click on watch sass

This will create 2 files filename.map.css and filname.css
Link filename.css with your html documnet

6.Now write SASS code in filename.scss it will be compiled in filename.css
Done